Setup

Requirements
Python 3.8+
PostgreSQL database with a table named cancerdata

Install dependencies
pip install pandas sqlalchemy scikit-learn matplotlib seaborn psycopg2

Configure database connection
Edit the connection string in your script:
engine = create_engine('postgresql://username:password@localhost:5432/your_db_name')

The database table should include the following fields:
patient_id
target_severity_score
age, gender, country_region, year, genetic_risk, air_pollution, alcohol_use, smoking, obesity_level, cancer_type, cancer_stage, treatment_cost_usd, survival_years

Example output:
Mean Squared Error: 2.35
RÂ² Score: 0.87

Interactive prediction
Run
python main.py

Then enter patient details when prompted.
